Code Specifications Naming conventions: 1、Package name: use lowercase letters, usually a combination of organisation name and function module name. 2, class name: using uppercase letters beginning with the camel-type naming, the 3、Method name: use lowercase letters to start the camel-type naming. 4, variable names: the use of lowercase letters beginning with the camel-type naming. 5, class annotations: use Javadoc annotations to describe the function of the class and author information. Method annotations: Use Javadoc annotations before each method, describing the method's function, parameters, and return value. 6, in-line comments: If necessary, use a single line comment to explain the complex logic. Structure specification: 7, interface methods: interface methods should be clear and consistent return type and parameter style. 8, method order: in accordance with the logical order of the methods. Return type: Return value: for query methods return an object or list, update or delete methods return an integer result (number of rows affected). Code Format: Use a consistent code format, leaving a blank line between each method.
